  "content": {
    "description": [
      ":doc",
      [
        ":h1",
        {
          "s": "App Pages and Widgets"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        [
          ":item-ref",
          {
            "s": "c4563df8-2eb4-4ad6-9502-5bf35b28e410"
          },
          {
            "s": "App Pages"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " are grid-based interactive pages composed from widget items. They use Hobson's existing item and attachment infrastructure — a page is an item, each widget is an item, and the page holds widgets as attachments with grid positioning."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":h2",
        {
          "s": "Architecture"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "The system uses three existing mechanisms:"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":ol",
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            [
              ":strong",
              {
                "s": "Attachments array"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " — widget items are attachments of the page item, exactly as spatial container children are"
            }
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            [
              ":strong",
              {
                "s": "Per-attachment view configuration"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " — the "
            },
            [
              ":code",
              {
                "s": "view"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " object on each attachment stores grid position ("
            },
            [
              ":code",
              {
                "s": "col"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": ", "
            },
            [
              ":code",
              {
                "s": "row"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": ", "
            },
            [
              ":code",
              {
                "s": "colSpan"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": ", "
            },
            [
              ":code",
              {
                "s": "rowSpan"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": ") rather than spatial coordinates"
            }
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            [
              ":strong",
              {
                "s": "View rendering"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " — each widget is rendered by its own view, resolved through the standard preference hierarchy"
            }
          ]
        ]
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "This is architecturally analogous to the spatial container, but with a CSS grid layout model and a shared state mechanism for inter-widget communication."
        }
      ],
      [
